<subsection xml:id="subsec-senstivity-specificity">
    <title>Sensitivity and Specificity</title>
    <p>
        Introduce the importance of these measurements.
    </p>
    <p>
        The <term>sensitivity</term> of a medical test indicates how well it <em>senses</em> the presence of an illness or condition. For example, a particular pregnancy test has 98% sensitivity when taken the first day of a missed period. 
    </p>
